	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Cooper's right; I think the C=64 Programmer's Reference Guide has the best freely available 6502 introduction out there. And yeah, you pretty much do have to test your code on real hardware to find out if it works (which is why I'm in the middle of trying to build an FDSLoadr cable...an approach that I'd recommend if you don't want to try and build a devcart.) As for NES-specific learning, the way I learned what I know, though probably not the best way for a lot of people, was just to pore over Yoshi's nestech doc, Firebug's mapper information, and Brad Taylor's sound reference until I understood it.

		

		</td>
